    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="149"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d149">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 P.W./9–2644</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chinese Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wei</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-26">September 26,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I have the honor to inform you
                    that I have just received the following telegraphic message, dated September 25,
                    1944, addressed by the President of the Republic of China to the President of
                    the United States of America: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“I am in receipt of your message of September 18 [<hi rend="italic"
                                >16</hi>], announcing the results of your Quebec conversations with
                            Prime Minister Churchill, for which I am most grateful. Chiang Kai
                            Shek”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>I shall be greatly obliged if you will be good enough to transmit the above
                    message to its high destination.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wei Tao-ming</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
